The Nigerian Meteorological Agency (NIMET), in its high-impact weather forecast released on Sunday, predicted severe heat in parts of Nigeria. According to its forecast, as observed by DAILY POST, parts of Kebbi, Sokoto, Katsina, Kano, Dutse, Bauchi, Nguru, and Borno indicate chances of experiencing high thermal discomfort. The forecast added that most parts of the Northern cities are expected to record temperatures between 35°C to 40°C. However, parts of Kebbi, Sokoto, Zamfara, Katsina, Kano, Jigawa, Bauchi, Gombe, Yobe and Borno States are expected to experience temperatures greater than 40°C. NiMet said while parts of Niger, Kaduna, FCT, Kwara, Kogi, Benue, Taraba, and Adamawa States are expected to record temperatures between 35°C to 40°C, parts of Enugu, Ebonyi, and Cross River will record temperatures between 35°C to 40°C. Parts of Enugu and Ebonyi States are also expected to record temperatures between 35°C to 40°C. Also on Monday May 16, it said parts of Kebbi, Sokoto, Zamfara, Katsina, Kano, Jigawa, Bauchi, Gombe, Yobe, Niger, and Borno States are expected to experience temperatures greater than 40°C.